Four bodies were found Sunday.  Jim Boling. The dams broke under the water pressure. Sixteen people remained missing. The death toll from flash floods that swept through a rural area of eastern Ohio rose to 20 Sunday as searchers dug along two creeks and dived into the Ohio River. No deaths or serious injuries were reported. Twenty-three dog teams from four states were searching for victims, said Boling. Across the border in West Virginia, Gov. Badia said rainwater running down hillsides forced debris into the creeks, forming dams at each bridge. Eventually the bridges couldn't hold any more. 